The paper proposes a method for training deep neural networks with fewer parameters, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus of the paper is on object recognition datasets, which suggests that it may fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the proposed method is applicable to various CNN architectures, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of overfitting, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the improvement in discriminative capability, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
